## II. LilyPond Example (Renderable Sheet Music)

> This is real notation software used by composers and engravers.

```lilypond
\version "2.24.0"

\score {
  <<
    % Primary Choir
    \new Staff = "Choir" <<
      \clef treble
      \time 4/4
      \key c \major
      \tempo 4 = 60
      \dynamicUp
      c'2\mf e'2\mf |
      g'2\mf e'2\mf |
    >>

    % Echo Return (Space)
    \new Staff = "Echo" <<
      \clef treble
      \time 4/4
      \key c \major
      \dynamicUp
      r2
      c'2~\p |
      c'2 e'2\pp |
      g'1~\ppp |
    >>
  >>
  \layout { }
}
```

### What This Encodes (Formally)

| Notation Choice | Meaning                        |
| --------------- | ------------------------------ |
| `r2` (rest)     | Echo latency                   |
| `~` (tie)       | Reverberation smear            |
| `p â†’ pp â†’ ppp`  | Energy decay                   |
| Identical pitch | Non-manipulative reinforcement |
| Separate staff  | Space â‰  agent                  |

This is **Î¼-safe awe**.

